OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1781547074
OL,3,CTwo men found guilty over arson
OL,4,Cattacks on properties linked to PM
OL,6,FTwo men have been found guilty of
OL,7,Fconspiring to commit an arson attack
OL,8,Fon houses and a car connected to Prime
OL,9,FMinister Sir Keir Starmer.
OL,11,FIn May 2025, a car owned by Starmer
OL,12,Fwas set alight in Kentish Town in
OL,13,Fnorth London and was later followed by
OL,14,Ftwo further attacks, including one
OL,15,Frented out to the PM's sister-in-law,
OL,16,Fwhich he still owned.
OL,18,FThe attacks, which were in the night,
OL,19,Fposed a serious threat to life and
OL,20,Fleft householders terrified, the Old
OL,21,FBailey heard.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
